      <details class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-7 py-5 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:text-blue-600 transition list-none">
          What is the minimum budget to start with Meta Ads?
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-7 pb-6 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          For local businesses on the Treasure Coast, well-segmented campaigns can work starting at $300–$500 per month. What matters most is not the total budget but how it is distributed: the right audience targeting, tested creatives, and a clear objective. Below $300, results tend to be limited because the algorithm needs data volume to optimize effectively.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-7 py-5 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:text-blue-600 transition list-none">
          How long does it take to see results from Facebook ads?
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-7 pb-6 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          The first few weeks are the learning phase. Month one is for testing and adjustment. From month two onward, results become more consistent and cost per result drops. Local businesses on the Treasure Coast typically see positive ROI within the first 3 months with well-managed campaigns.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-7 py-5 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:text-blue-600 transition list-none">
          Meta Ads or Google Ads — which is better for my local business?
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-7 pb-6 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          It depends on whether your customer already knows what they are looking for. <a href="/en/services/google-ads-treasure-coast/" class="font-medium hover:underline" style="color:var(--primary)">Google Ads</a> captures existing demand (the customer is already searching). Meta Ads creates new demand by reaching people who fit your ideal customer profile but have not discovered you yet. Visual businesses like restaurants and salons tend to perform better on Meta; urgent services like plumbers and dentists on Google.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
